<paragraph id="75FEFE5845940E399D2320C047E6D030" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D5BB84E5907CFE0848804A35D26D251B" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">
This variety differ from 
<taxonomicName id="2946CE598BE3BF4A29C739AF17BDAA38" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Croton" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Croton manampetsae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="manampetsae">
<emphasis id="8F73496DF5334F0405BEC982B1A51218" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Croton manampetsae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in that the leaves are mostly alternate (vs. opposite) and in the lepidote indumentum on the abaxial side of the leaves (vs. stellate trichomes). It will likely be described as a distinct species.
</paragraph>
